# Example user themes file, copy to ./themes.yml at the root of your
# project to:
#   - change the default theme without passing --theme each time
#   - override a built-in theme (re-declare it with the same name:)
#   - add your own custom themes
#
# See .agents/rules/eco-design.md and .agents/rules/accessibility.md
# for the constraints (system fonts only, WCAG AA contrasts).
#
# Visual identity: "Blueprint", flat fills with hairline frames, a
# vertical rail connecting steps. The colour schema below mirrors that
# system; do not re-introduce gradient fields.

# Make 'dark' the default for this project, overrides the built-in
# default of 'light'. Comment out to keep 'light'.
default: dark

